## Implementation Plan — Smartphone Accelerometer Data for Variometer Aid

**Problem Statement:**
The Android accelerometer is already subscribed at startup and delivers 3-axis values to `OnAccelerationSensor(float ddx, float ddy, float ddz)` — but that handler is a `// TODO` stub. The goal is to wire those values through the data pipeline (`NMEAInfo` → `MoreData` → `BasicComputer`) so a future merging algorithm can consume them alongside the existing barometric/GPS vario.

**Background:**
- `AccelerationState` in `src/NMEA/Acceleration.hpp` holds only a scalar `g_load` + `available`/`real` flags.
- `NMEAInfo` embeds `AccelerationState acceleration` and is the canonical per-device sensor data struct. It is `static_assert`ed as trivial — all new fields must keep it trivially constructible.
- `BasicComputer::Compute()` runs in `MergeThread` — event-triggered, once per incoming sensor event, rate-limited to max 20 Hz by `period_min=50ms`.
- Android accelerometer is subscribed with `SENSOR_DELAY_NORMAL` (nominal 200ms / 5Hz hint, actual varies). Needs to change to `SENSOR_DELAY_GAME` (≈20ms / 50Hz) for FIR filter usefulness.
- `Device/Factory.cpp` unconditionally subscribes to `TYPE_ACCELEROMETER` — keep this as-is (Task 4 skipped).
- Settings pattern: `FeaturesSettings` in `src/Computer/Settings.hpp`, persisted in `src/Profile/ComputerProfile.cpp`, UI in `src/Dialogs/Settings/Panels/GlideComputerConfigPanel.cpp`, key in `src/Profile/Keys.hpp`.
- Future FIR filter history buffer belongs in `BasicComputer` as a member (like `FilteredVarioComputer`), not in `NMEAInfo`.

---

### Task 1: Extend `AccelerationState` with raw 3-axis vector + timestamp

**Objective:** Add `accel_x`, `accel_y`, `accel_z` (m/s², device frame), `raw_available` flag, and `raw_timestamp` (TimeStamp) to `AccelerationState`.

**Files to modify:**
- `src/NMEA/Acceleration.hpp`
- `src/NMEA/Acceleration.cpp` (update `Complement()`)

**Implementation:**

In `src/NMEA/Acceleration.hpp`, add to `AccelerationState`:
```cpp
#include "time/Stamp.hpp"  // for TimeStamp — add include at top

struct AccelerationState
{
  bool available;
  bool real;
  double g_load;

  // Raw 3-axis accelerometer vector (m/s², device frame), from internal sensor
  bool raw_available;
  TimeStamp raw_timestamp;
  float accel_x, accel_y, accel_z;

  void Reset() {
    available = false;
    raw_available = false;
  }

  void ProvideGLoad(double _g_load, bool _real=true) noexcept {
    g_load = _g_load;
    real = _real;
    available = true;
  }

  void ProvideRawAcceleration(TimeStamp t, float x, float y, float z) noexcept {
    raw_timestamp = t;
    accel_x = x;
    accel_y = y;
    accel_z = z;
    raw_available = true;
  }

  void Complement(const AccelerationState &add);
};
```

In `src/NMEA/Acceleration.cpp`, update `Complement()` to also complement the raw fields:
```cpp
void
AccelerationState::Complement(const AccelerationState &add)
{
  if (!available && add.available)
    ProvideGLoad(add.g_load, add.real);

  if (!raw_available && add.raw_available)
    ProvideRawAcceleration(add.raw_timestamp, add.accel_x, add.accel_y, add.accel_z);
}
```

**Test:** The existing `static_assert(std::is_trivial<NMEAInfo>::value)` must still pass. Build and verify.

**Demo:** Compiles cleanly; existing tests pass.

---

### Task 2: Add `accel_vario_enabled` setting to `FeaturesSettings`

**Objective:** Introduce a boolean opt-in setting, persisted to profile, defaulting to false.

**Files to modify:**
- `src/Computer/Settings.hpp` — add field to `FeaturesSettings`
- `src/Computer/Settings.cpp` — set default to false
- `src/Profile/Keys.hpp` — add profile key
- `src/Profile/ComputerProfile.cpp` — load from profile

**Implementation:**

In `src/Computer/Settings.hpp`, add to `FeaturesSettings`:
```cpp
bool accel_vario_enabled;
```

In `src/Computer/Settings.cpp` `FeaturesSettings::SetDefaults()`:
```cpp
accel_vario_enabled = false;
```

In `src/Profile/Keys.hpp`:
```cpp
constexpr std::string_view AccelVarioEnabled = "AccelVarioEnabled";
```

In `src/Profile/ComputerProfile.cpp`, in `Profile::Load(const ProfileMap &map, FeaturesSettings &settings)`:
```cpp
map.Get(ProfileKeys::AccelVarioEnabled, settings.accel_vario_enabled);
```

**Demo:** Setting defaults to false; survives profile save/load round-trip.

---

### Task 3: Expose the setting in `GlideComputerConfigPanel`

**Objective:** User-visible toggle in Settings → Glide Computer, Android-only, expert row.

**Files to modify:**
- `src/Dialogs/Settings/Panels/GlideComputerConfigPanel.cpp`

**Implementation:**

Add `AccelVarioEnabled` to `ControlIndex` enum (inside `#ifdef ANDROID`... or just add the enum value always but guard the `AddBoolean` call).

Better: add the enum value unconditionally, guard the Add/Save calls with `#ifdef ANDROID`:

```cpp
// in enum ControlIndex:
AccelVarioEnabled,

// in Prepare(), after WaveAssistant row:
#ifdef ANDROID
  AddBoolean(_("Accel. vario aid"),
             _("Use the smartphone accelerometer to aid the variometer (Android only)."),
             settings_computer.features.accel_vario_enabled);
  SetExpertRow(AccelVarioEnabled);
#endif

// in Save():
#ifdef ANDROID
  changed |= SaveValue(AccelVarioEnabled, ProfileKeys::AccelVarioEnabled,
                       settings_computer.features.accel_vario_enabled);
#endif
```

**Demo:** Toggle visible in expert rows on Android; persists across restart.

---

### Task 4: Handle `OnAccelerationSensor(float ddx, float ddy, float ddz)` — store in `NMEAInfo`, and increase sensor rate

**Objective:** Implement the previously stubbed 3-axis callback; increase Android sensor rate to SENSOR_DELAY_GAME for FIR-usable sampling.

**Files to modify:**
- `src/Device/AndroidSensors.cpp` — implement the stub
- `android/src/NonGPSSensors.java` — change `SENSOR_DELAY_NORMAL` to `SENSOR_DELAY_GAME`

**Implementation:**

In `src/Device/AndroidSensors.cpp`, replace the `// TODO` stub:
```cpp
void
DeviceDescriptor::OnAccelerationSensor(float ddx, float ddy, float ddz) noexcept
{
  const auto e = BeginEdit();
  NMEAInfo &basic = *e;
  basic.UpdateClock();
  basic.alive.Update(basic.clock);
  basic.acceleration.ProvideRawAcceleration(basic.clock, ddx, ddy, ddz);
  e.Commit();
}
```

In `android/src/NonGPSSensors.java`, change the subscription line:
```java
// Before:
sensor_manager_.registerListener(this, default_sensors_[id],
                                 sensor_manager_.SENSOR_DELAY_NORMAL);
// After:
sensor_manager_.registerListener(this, default_sensors_[id],
                                 SensorManager.SENSOR_DELAY_GAME);
```

Note: `SENSOR_DELAY_GAME` applies to ALL subscribed sensors (accelerometer, gyroscope, magnetometer, pressure). Pressure was previously on NORMAL (~5Hz). If this causes issues, the subscription can be split per sensor type inside `run()`. For now, the unified change is acceptable.

**Demo:** LogCat shows `accel_x/y/z` values arriving at ~50Hz and being stored in `NMEAInfo`.

---

### Task 5: Add `AccelVarioComputer` stub inside `BasicComputer`

**Objective:** Create an `AccelVarioComputer` class owning a timestamped ring buffer of raw accel samples. Wire it into `BasicComputer::Compute()`. No filtering logic yet — just accumulates samples ready for the future algorithm.

**Files to create:**
- `src/Computer/AccelVarioComputer.hpp`
- `src/Computer/AccelVarioComputer.cpp`

**Files to modify:**
- `src/Computer/BasicComputer.hpp` — add member
- `src/Computer/BasicComputer.cpp` — call from `Compute()`

**Implementation:**

`src/Computer/AccelVarioComputer.hpp`:
```cpp
#pragma once

#include "time/Stamp.hpp"
#include <array>

struct MoreData;
struct FeaturesSettings;

struct AccelSample {
  TimeStamp t;
  float x, y, z;
};

/**
 * Collects raw accelerometer samples for variometer aiding.
 * Maintains a ring buffer of recent samples for future FIR filtering.
 */
class AccelVarioComputer {
  static constexpr std::size_t HISTORY_SIZE = 64;

  std::array<AccelSample, HISTORY_SIZE> history;
  std::size_t head = 0;
  std::size_t count = 0;

public:
  void Reset() noexcept {
    head = 0;
    count = 0;
  }

  /**
   * Push a new sample if raw acceleration is available and the setting is enabled.
   * Call once per BasicComputer::Compute() invocation.
   */
  void Update(const MoreData &data, const FeaturesSettings &features) noexcept;
};
```

`src/Computer/AccelVarioComputer.cpp`:
```cpp
#include "AccelVarioComputer.hpp"
#include "NMEA/MoreData.hpp"
#include "Computer/Settings.hpp"

void
AccelVarioComputer::Update(const MoreData &data,
                           const FeaturesSettings &features) noexcept
{
  if (!features.accel_vario_enabled || !data.acceleration.raw_available)
    return;

  AccelSample &s = history[head];
  s.t = data.acceleration.raw_timestamp;
  s.x = data.acceleration.accel_x;
  s.y = data.acceleration.accel_y;
  s.z = data.acceleration.accel_z;

  head = (head + 1) % HISTORY_SIZE;
  if (count < HISTORY_SIZE)
    ++count;

  // TODO: AccelVario — run FIR filter over history buffer here
  // and write result to data.brutto_vario or a new accel_vario field
}
```

In `src/Computer/BasicComputer.hpp`, add member:
```cpp
#include "AccelVarioComputer.hpp"

class BasicComputer {
  GroundSpeedComputer ground_speed;
  FilteredVarioComputer filtered_vario;
  AccelVarioComputer accel_vario;   // <-- add this
  ...
};
```

In `src/Computer/BasicComputer.cpp`, add call at end of `Compute()`:
```cpp
accel_vario.Update(data, settings.features);
```

Also reset it in any Reset path if one exists (check if BasicComputer has a Reset — it doesn't currently, but AccelVarioComputer::Reset() is available when needed).

**Build:** Compile the project and verify no errors.

**Demo:** End-to-end: phone moves → `OnAccelerationSensor` fires → stored in `NMEAInfo` → `AccelVarioComputer::Update()` appends to ring buffer. History buffer fills with timestamped samples. Codebase is ready for the FIR algorithm task.

